e magnified yellow-green mildew texture, where the clustered growth appears to break up or cloud over as if being attacked or dissolved. The stained grout returns with white on-screen text at the bottom reading “ELAPSED TIME 5 MINUTES.” Over several moments, the brown-orange staining along the grout appears lighter and less dense, especially along the horizontal line, while water droplets remain scattered on the surrounding blue tiles. The cross-shaped grout intersection is still visible, but the area looks progressively cleaner and paler compared with the earlier darker, dirtier buildup. The product bottle is then brought into view in front of the blue tiled wall. A right hand holds a white Tilex trigger-spray bottle upright on a glass shelf or ledge. The bottle has a blue label with a tile-grid design and the large white Tilex logo across it, with smaller yellow text beneath. After holding it steady for display, the hand lets go, leaving the bottle standing centered against the neat blue tile background. Finally, the woman appears again in the bathroom, now out of the shower and wrapped in a white towel around her body. She has wet dark hair and holds another white towel up to one side of her head, drying her hair. The lighting remains cool blue and purple, with a round ceiling light glowing above her. She stands calmly in the bathroom, no longer pressed against the tile, as the clean, steamy shower setting remains in the background.",
